---
import VizPlaceholder from '../../VizPlaceholder.astro';

const toc = [
  { num: '01', label: 'The question', href: '#why' },
  { num: '02', label: 'Your work', href: '#work-shift' },
  { num: '03', label: 'The barrier', href: '#barrier' },
  { num: '04', label: 'Capabilities', href: '#capabilities' },
  { num: '05', label: 'Knowledge', href: '#knowledge' },
  { num: '06', label: 'Landscape', href: '#landscape' },
];
---

<section id="top" class="px-6 pt-20 pb-16 md:pt-28 md:pb-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-accent">
      An educational reference
    </p>
    <h1
      class="mt-6 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 sm:text-6xl"
    >
      What is a meta-harness?
    </h1>
    <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-xl text-lg text-neutral-400 sm:text-xl">
      Answered in one breath, then unpacked.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-5xl">
    <VizPlaceholder label="MetaHarnessLayers island" ratio="aspect-[16/10]" />
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-neutral-200">
      At the core, a large language model predicts tokens. A
      <mark>harness</mark> wraps that model into an agent that can act, reading
      files, running commands, calling tools. Claude Code, Codex, and OpenCode
      are harnesses. A <mark>meta-harness</mark> wraps the harness, operating
      above one or more of them across everything a single agent never sees on
      its own: many repositories, many sessions, many people, and time.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
      That is the whole concept. The model at the center, the harness around it,
      the meta-harness around both. Everything below is the answer to the next
      question: why would you want one?
    </p>
  </div>

  <nav aria-label="Sections" class="mx-auto mt-16 max-w-5xl">
    <ul
      class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-neutral-900 bg-neutral-900 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-6"
    >
      {
        toc.map((item) => (
          <li>
            <a
              href={item.href}
              class="flex h-full flex-col gap-1.5 bg-neutral-950 p-4 transition-colors hover:bg-neutral-900/60"
            >
              <span class="font-mono text-xs text-neutral-600">{item.num}</span>
              <span class="text-sm text-neutral-300">{item.label}</span>
            </a>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
  </nav>
</section>
